                            <div class="accord-content">
                                <p>
                                    <b>NO,</b> we at Sports Injury Centre are managing knee
                                    pain in young people with a very scientific and patient
                                    specific approach which requires HKA axis Xray to
                                    diagnose tibia vara, if found it can be corrected surgically
                                    by high tibial osteotomy and hence patient’s knee joint
                                    can be saved from total knee replacement, the surgery
                                    being termed as <b>‘KNEE SALVAGE SURGERY’ OR ‘GREEN KNEE SURGERY’</b>
                                    as termed by us.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <!--End single accordion box-->
                        <!--Start single accordion box-->
                        <div class="accordion accordion-block">
                            <div class="accord-btn">
                                <h4>
                                    Should we consider meniscal tears at younger age significantly important?
                                </h4>
                            </div>
                            <div class="accord-content">
                                <p>
                                    <b>YES,</b> meniscus are the semicircular shocking
                                    absorbing elastic discs which helps protect bone and
                                    articular cartilage from vertical and shear stress, if they
                                    are damaged then if this meniscal damage is neglected
                                    then can lead to early osteoarthritis
                                </p>
                            </div>
